It was a bit of a walk to central downtown, but the low price for a hotel room as nice as the larger downtown hotels I have stayed in was well worth it.	I really don't have anything bad to say about this hotel, the price is a little steep per night but it is definitely worth it.	The buffet breakfast is really quite good and worth the price if you are hungry.	For a price of $10 we had a choice of hot and cold items, both ready made, and made to order.	The room-rate of this hotel was much less expensive than others and we had a perfect stay.